0 "" {TEXT 256 34 "Introduction to Graphing Functions" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 179 "Save your current wor
ksheet as work04-yourlastname.mws.  Remember to save frequently to avo
id losing data in case that the system would shut down in the middle o
f a work session! " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 104 "In the text mode (click on the cap T button) place your \+
name(s) and date at the top of your worksheet.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 31 "1.  Graphing functions and the " }{TEXT 257 4 "plot" }{TEXT -1 
89 " command.  The Maple command for plotting the graph of an explicit
ly defined function is:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " }{TEXT 258 0 "" }{TEXT 259 4 "plot" }{TEXT 
260 0 "" }{TEXT -1 2 "( " }{TEXT 261 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 
266 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 20 "=range [, options]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 262 4 "expr" }
{TEXT 267 1 " " }{TEXT -1 24 "is a symbolic expression" }{TEXT 264 1 "
 " }{TEXT -1 48 "which represents the function to be plotted and " }
{TEXT 263 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 38 " is the independent variable used in  " 
}{TEXT 265 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 25 "  to define the function." }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 81 "Several options
 exist to change way the plot will appear.  These options include:" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 126 "        \+
    y=range                       this allows the user to specifiy the
 range of output values which Maple will display" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 113 "            thickness=value           this controls the \+
thickness of the plotted curve.  value = 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 119 "            color=value                 this sets
 the color of the plotted curve.  value = red, green, blue, cyan, etc.
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 160 "For \+
each of the following functions provide a plot to represent the graph \+
the function.  Choose a range that will optimally represent the featur
es of the graph." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 16 "a.    y = 3x - 1" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
